sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Spark Operator Controller
    participant SparkSubmit as spark-submit<br/>(subprocess)
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod
    participant Executors as Spark Executor Pods
    participant ConnectSvc as SparkConnect Service<br/>15002/TCP

    Note over User,Executors: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: POST SparkApplication CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-sparkapplication<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (validated)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-sparkapplication<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (defaulted)
    K8sAPI-->>User: SparkApplication created

    Note over Controller: Reconcile loop detects new SparkApplication<br/>State: New → Submitted

    Controller->>SparkSubmit: Local exec (29-stage arg pipeline)
    SparkSubmit->>K8sAPI: Create Driver Pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Note over Webhook: Injects 26 categories of config:<br/>env vars, volumes, security contexts,<br/>scheduler, sidecars, Prometheus annotations
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod spec

    SparkSubmit->>K8sAPI: Create Executor Pods<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod (per executor)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod specs

    Note over Controller: State: Submitted → Running<br/>Monitors driver/executor pods

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create {app}-ui-svc Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create {app}-ui-ingress (if configured)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Controller: State: Running → Succeeding → Completed<br/>TTL-based cleanup

    Note over User,ConnectSvc: Flow 2: ScheduledSparkApplication Cron Execution

    Note over Controller: Cron trigger fires
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create child SparkApplication CR<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Note over Controller: Triggers Flow 1 reconciliation<br/>Concurrency: Allow/Forbid/Replace

    Note over User,ConnectSvc: Flow 3: SparkConnect Server Lifecycle

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap, Pod, Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    User->>ConnectSvc: Spark Connect client<br/>15002/TCP Spark Connect protocol<br/>Auth: None
    ConnectSvc->>Executors: Spark RPC<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP<br/>Encryption: None
